{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T04:48:05.866Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Early stopping"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is a regularization technique that prevents overfitting by "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "halting the training process before the model starts memorizing noise or irrelevant patterns"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in the training data, specifically by monitoring a validation metric and stopping when it stops improving for a predefined number of epochs."}]}, {"type": "blockquote", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Simple definition:"}, {"type": "text", "text": " \"Early stopping is a regularization technique used in machine learning to prevent overfitting during the training of a model by monitoring the model's performance on a validation dataset and stopping when performance starts to deteriorate.\""}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Early Stopping — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What overfitting is in training"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "During training, models typically follow this pattern:"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Initial phase"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Model improves on "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "both training and validation data"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Overfitting point"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Validation performance "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "plateaus or degrades"}, {"type": "text", "text": " while training performance "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "continues to improve"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Memorization"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Model starts fitting "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "noise"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in training data"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "This "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "divergence"}, {"type": "text", "text": " between training and validation loss indicates overfitting:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Training loss:  ↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓↓ (continues decreasing)\nValidation loss: ↓↓↓↓____↑↑↑ (starts increasing after epoch 6)\n                          ↑\n                  Overfitting begins here"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How early stopping works"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Dataset Splitting"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Split dataset into three parts:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Set"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Purpose"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Training set"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Update model weights"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Validation set"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Monitor model performance"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Test set"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Evaluate final model"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "[vtiya.medium](https://vtiya.medium.com/how-early-stopping-does-prevent-overfitting-3bba0e33598b)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Model Training"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "During training:\n- Iteratively update parameters using "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "training data"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n- After each "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "epoch"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (one pass through training data), evaluate on "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "validation set"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Monitoring Validation Loss"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Track a metric on validation set as training progresses:\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Validation loss"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (most common)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Accuracy"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Mean squared error"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n- Other performance metrics"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "4. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Patience Parameter"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Patience"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = number of epochs allowed to continue training after validation loss stops improving:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "If validation loss doesn't improve for "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "patience epochs"}, {"type": "text", "text": " → trigger early stopping"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Example: patience = 5 → stop if no improvement for 5 consecutive epochs"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "5. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Stopping Criteria"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When validation loss doesn't improve for patience period:\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Stop training"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n- Model weights at stopping point = final weights"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "6. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Retaining the Best Model"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common practice: "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "save model weights at the epoch with lowest validation loss"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Epoch 1: val_loss = 0.50\nEpoch 2: val_loss = 0.45\nEpoch 3: val_loss = 0.40  ← Best (lowest)\nEpoch 4: val_loss = 0.42\nEpoch 5: val_loss = 0.45\nEpoch 6: val_loss = 0.48  ← Stop here (patience = 3)\n                             Save weights from Epoch 3"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Implementation in TensorFlow (Keras)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from tensorflow.keras.callbacks import EarlyStopping\n\n# Create EarlyStopping callback\nearly_stopping = EarlyStopping(\n    monitor='val_loss',        # Metric to monitor\n    patience=10,               # Epochs to wait before stopping\n    restore_best_weights=True  # Restore weights from best epoch\n)\n\n# Use in model training\nmodel.fit(\n    X_train, y_train,\n    validation_data=(X_val, y_val),\n    epochs=100,\n    callbacks=[early_stopping]\n)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key parameters"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "monitor"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Performance measure to track (e.g., "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "val_loss"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "val_accuracy"}, {"type": "text", "text": ")\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "patience"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Number of epochs with no improvement after which training stops\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "restore_best_weights"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Whether to restore weights from epoch with best monitored value"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "[codesignal](https://codesignal.com/learn/courses/modeling-the-iris-dataset-with-tensorflow/lessons/implementing-early-stopping-in-tensorflow-to-prevent-overfitting)"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Implementation in PyTorch"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import torch\n\nbest_val_loss = float('inf')\npatience = 5\npatience_counter = 0\n\nfor epoch in range(num_epochs):\n    # Train for one epoch\n    train_loss = train_one_epoch(model, train_loader)\n    \n    # Evaluate on validation\n    val_loss = evaluate(model, val_loader)\n    \n    # Early stopping check\n    if val_loss < best_val_loss:\n        best_val_loss = val_loss\n        patience_counter = 0\n        torch.save(model.state_dict(), 'best_model.pth')  # Save best\n    else:\n        patience_counter += 1\n        if patience_counter >= patience:\n            print(f\"Early stopping at epoch {epoch}\")\n            break"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why early stopping prevents overfitting"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Early stopping prevents overfitting by:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mechanism"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Effect"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Halts training early"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Stops before model memorizes noise"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Retains generalization ability"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Model keeps ability to generalize to unseen data"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Prevents learning noise"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Doesn't learn training data's noise/outliers too precisely"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Creates robust model"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Results in robust model that generalizes well"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key advantage"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Doesn't require modifying model architecture or loss function (unlike dropout or weight decay)."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Advantages of early stopping"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Advantage"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Description"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Prevents overfitting"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Stops learning noise, ensures better generalization"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Efficiency"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Significantly reduces training time"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Saves resources"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Avoids unnecessary epochs, saves computational resources"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Adaptable"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Automatically adjusts stopping point based on observed performance"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Simple"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "No architecture changes needed; just add a callback"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "[milvus](https://milvus.io/ai-quick-reference/how-does-early-stopping-prevent-overfitting-in-deep-learning)"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key trade-off: Choosing patience"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "patience value"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is crucial:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Patience Value"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, 